Insight route waits for the user to finish authenticating.

Changes to support firebase security

Do to limited data available during firebase auth, we have to use user.id as the key for the user object. The drawback to this is the id happens to be the users e-mail. This change sets up all the ownership references to use an id that can be public.
Set id when using firebase.find()

Query controller creates a global query then saves a link to it under MyQuery
Stop observing value changes when the view is unloaded.
Name, description and query have been promoted to the insight object. They're no longer retrieved from within the spec file.

Prevent excessive query duplication

Saves queries in a global list, query authors have multiple MyQuery objects which reference the global queries. 

MyQueries  are what's shown in the browser.
